description.plain: Rosie Tucker is a Los Angeles-based indie singer/songwriter, whose musical influences include cult-favorite songwriters of the 1960s such as Dusty Springfield, Buffy Sainte-Marie, and Sibylle Baier. Their work has received widespread critical acclaim from publications including NPR, Stereogum, and Paste, and they have performed alongside acts like Phoebe Bridgers, Soccer Mommy, Vagabon, and Remo Drive.
